page.title: 06Wildflowers/Trees, New Deer
page.content: The following selection of some of the wild flowers can be found in this area; {Rosebay willowherb Daisy {White deadnettle Dock {Henbit deadnettle Bluebell {Ground elder Sweet cecily {Pineapple mayweed Feverfew {Pink purslane Corn daisy {Birds foot trefoil Bistort {Purple tufted vetch Eyebright {Scottish thistle Broom {Gorse Foxglove The most common trees found in the area are; {Sycamore, Beech, Hawthorn, Elder, {Ash, Alder, Spruce. A few examples of{Scots pine}are also to be found.
